# Subagents enabled

All custom subagents in `.cursor/agents/` are **enabled**. Delegate with the Task tool using `subagent_type` or invoke with `/name`.

## Creative pipeline (use in order when building scenery)

1. **command-interpreter** — clarify vague commands (10-pass review + 4 options)
2. **inspiration-scout** — web research and mood/direction brief
3. **asset-curator** — pick Kenney assets from `res://assets/`
4. **asset-placer** — place props in Godot scenes

## Game and visuals

5. **game-rebuilder** — rebuild gameplay, tracks, cars, UI, physics from user commands
6. **graphics-improver** — lighting, materials, post-processing, visual polish

## User-level (also available)

7. **skill-synthesizer** — create Agent Skills when repeated workflows appear

## Built-in subagents (also enabled)

Use Task tool `subagent_type` when appropriate: `explore`, `shell`, `generalPurpose`, `cursor-guide`, `ci-investigator`, `bugbot`, `security-review`, `best-of-n-runner`.

Prefer project subagents for Godot/asset work; use built-in types for codebase search, terminal, or review tasks.
